    {
      "offset_seconds": 47,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 10,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "And it looks like you're eligible for a reward for your goals, um, 'cause you completed two skills in seven days, so nice job.",

    {
      "offset_seconds": 58,
      "event_type": "view_change",

    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 59,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Um..."
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 101,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 12,
      "speaker_label": "background",
      "text": "Iris met her cousin at the diner for breakfast at 8:02 a.m. They spent 48 minutes at the diner. Part 1: Click on the number line that shows the time they spent at the diner."
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 114,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 9,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "And it looks like the system is suggesting that you lower your problems completed to 22 instead of 30. Does that sound okay to you?",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 123,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Uh, yeah.",
      "speaker_name": "Darrell Buffalo Ball"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 125,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Yeah? Okay.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 127,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 3,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "So... Oh, yeah?",
      "speaker_name": "Darrell Buffalo Ball"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 131,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 8,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Yeah, so that sounds good to you instead of completing 30 problems completing like 22 instead as your goal?",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 140,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Okay. Uh, how much did I complete right now?",
      "speaker_name": "Darrell Buffalo Ball"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 143,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Um, it says 13 problems.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 148,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Okay, so I should slow down?",

      "duration_seconds": 1,

    {

      "x": null,

      "details": null
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 235,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 13,
      "speaker_label": "background",
      "text": "Rabia drove home from the grocery store after she bought her groceries. She did not check the time when she left the grocery store, but she knew it took her 33 minutes to drive home. It was 1:44 p.m. when she got home."
    },
    {

    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 322,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 9,
      "speaker_label": "background",
      "text": "McKenna finished her math quiz at 9:35 a.m. She did not check the time when she started, but her computer showed that she spent 28 minutes on the quiz."
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 331,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 6,
      "speaker_label": "background",

    {

    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 344,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 7,
      "speaker_label": "background",
      "text": "Maggie finished her piano lesson at 4:51 p.m. She did not look at the time when she started, but she knows her lesson lasts for 45 minutes."
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 351,
      "event_type": "view_change",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "description": "Switch to gallery view with tutor and a new student (Taylynn)"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 352,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Hi, how's it going?",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 359,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 4,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Uh, you're muted right now so I can't hear you right now but...",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 404,
      "event_type": "inactivity",
      "duration_seconds": 10,
      "description": "Student gestures"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 414,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 4,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "There should be kind of like a microphone looking button that says audio. Yeah.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 418,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Um, I'm... I'm stuck.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 421,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 5,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "You're stuck? Okay. If you could share your screen so I can see what you're working on that'd be helpful.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 427,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Okay.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 430,
      "event_type": "view_change",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "description": "Student shares screen showing Moby Max interface"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 432,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Okay.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 433,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "I'm working on this.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 447,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 8,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Okay. So... Which... I guess which step in these like how they're showing you how to do it, which step do you get stuck on?",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 508,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 3,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Uh, like I don't I don't like get it.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 512,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 8,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Okay. So for these questions we're supposed to be solving for x. Mhm. So we have 1/2 divided by 1/4 equals x over 1.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 525,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 526,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 12,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "So a way that we can solve for that is by cross multiplying. So we would do 1/2 times 1, so that's how they got 1/2 on the left. And then they did 1/4 times x, which is how they got x times 1/4 over on the right.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 546,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Does that part make sense?",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 549,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "No.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 550,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 4,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "No? Okay. That's okay. Let me... I don't know if you can see me drawing...",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 558,
      "event_type": "drawing",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "tool": "shape",
      "target_desc": "green box around the problem",
      "details": "Tutor draws a green box"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 600,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "I was gonna draw... Oh woah.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 603,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Um... Okay.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 604,
      "event_type": "view_change",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "description": "Student stops screen sharing, returning to gallery view"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 606,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "There we go.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 609,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Uh, oh yeah I can draw this way too.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 613,
      "event_type": "view_change",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "description": "Tutor shares whiteboard screen"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 617,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Okay.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 619,
      "event_type": "drawing",
      "duration_seconds": 15,
      "tool": "pen",
      "target_desc": "whiteboard",
      "details": "Tutor writes 1/2 over 1/4 = x/1"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 641,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 6,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "So the first thing that they do... So we're trying to solve for x is the goal.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 647,
      "event_type": "drawing",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "tool": "pen",
      "target_desc": "cross multiplication arrows",
      "details": "Tutor draws red arrows crossing the fractions"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 648,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "So they multiply these two.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 653,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "And then they multiply these two.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 655,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Oh, the butterfly method.",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 657,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 1,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "Okay. Yeah.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 659,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 10,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "So whatever is on the top is the side that we go on. So like 1/2 times 1 is 1/2.",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 668,
      "event_type": "drawing",
      "duration_seconds": 4,
      "tool": "pen",
      "target_desc": "whiteboard",
      "details": "Tutor writes 1/2 ="
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 711,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 12,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "And since 1/2 is on the left side of the equal sign, it stays on the left side. And then the x is on the right hand side, so when you're multiplying by 1/4 it'll be...",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 723,
      "event_type": "drawing",
      "duration_seconds": 5,
      "tool": "pen",
      "target_desc": "whiteboard",
      "details": "Tutor writes x over 1/4 (looks like x times 1/4 notation)"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 732,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 4,
      "speaker_label": "tutor",
      "text": "And then once you have this, what's a way to get x by itself?",
      "speaker_name": "Katy Jones"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 737,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
      "duration_seconds": 2,
      "speaker_label": "student",
      "text": "Um... subtract?",
      "speaker_name": "Taylynn Tanewasha"
    },
    {
      "offset_seconds": 741,
      "event_type": "spoken_utterance",
